> On one of our linux servers, we're getting a lot of messages
> similar to the
> following:
>
> Jul 13 10:05:57 HOST kernel: hda: timeout waiting for DMA
> Jul 13 10:05:57 HOST kernel: hda: irq timeout: status=0x58
> DriveReady SeekComplete DataRequest }
I had similar messages on an old 486 I use for a gateway. I did get some
data loss when the kernel couldn't recover from the disk timeouts and a
reset was required. In the end I reverted back to 2.2.13 which seems to be
the last stable kernel WRT this issue.
